(1) when type python in command window, if it gives error as "python.exe" is not recognized as an internal or external command, then need to add pythonpath to windows system path
To add the path to the python.exe file to the Path variable, 
https://geek-university.com/python/add-python-to-the-windows-path/
(2) PyInstaller is installed from visual studio 2019 in C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\Shared\Python37_64\Lib\site-packages\
(3) in solution folder, command window input python -m PyInstaller MyProgram.py, then it build the python code into exe file
python -m PyInstaller --onefile MyProgram.py then build into just one exe file
